<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.190.78164.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A-P Navicula winoniformis Chudaev, Glushchenko, Kulikovskiy & Kociolek, sp. nov. LM, DIC. Size diminution series. Vietnam, slides no 00269 (A), 00318 (L, P, N), 00323 (I), 00326 (C), 00328 (B), 02079 (O), 03572 (E, F, H, K, M), 03773 (D), 04853 (J). Laos, slide no 00956 (G). Holotype (E). Scale bar: 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647957" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.190.78164.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. A-F Navicula winoniformis Chudaev, Glushchenko, Kulikovskiy & Kociolek, sp. nov. SEM. Sample no 03572. A-C external views D-F internal views A, D the whole valve B, E central area C, F valve end. A black arrows show the terminal raphe fissures. White arrow shows the indistinct kink of raphe branch B white arrows show central raphe pores. Black arrow shows the very slightly elevated raphe-sternum C black arrow shows the terminal raphe fissure. White arrow shows the longitudinal grooves where areola openings are located. White arrowheads show the small isolated apical areolae D white arrows show the accessory rib E black arrow shows the rectangular areola opening. Black arrowhead shows the circular areola opening. White arrows show the central raphe endings. White arrowhead shows the raphe slit F black arrows show the stria which are slightly wider than virgae. White arrow shows the helicroglossa. White arrowheads show the small isolated apical areolae. Scale bars: 5 μm (A); 2 μm (B-E); 1 μm (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647958" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

